abstract: Judge Susan Bolton of United States District Court in Phoenix dismisses lawsuit by Arizona Gov Jan Brewer that had accused Obama administration of failing to enforce immigration laws or maintain control of her state's border with Mexico; says that governor's claim is a political question that is not appropriate for the court to decide.
snippet: A federal judge said that Gov. Jan Brewer had raised a political question in claiming that the Obama administration did not properly control the border.
lead_paragraph: A federal judge said that Gov. Jan Brewer had raised a political question in claiming that the Obama administration did not properly control the border.

headline.main: Judge Dismisses Arizona Suit on Immigration Enforcement
headline.print_headline: Judge Dismisses Arizona Suit On Immigration Enforcement
